&lt;h2 id=&#34;context&#34;&gt;Context&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tail latency&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the slowest response times experienced by a small percentage of requests in a system. These are typically measured at the &lt;strong&gt;99th percentile (p99) or 99.9th percentile (p999)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
